Upgrade procedure for ldns

Source: https://nlnetlabs.nl/downloads/ldns/ldns-VERSION.tar.gz

To upgrade to a new version:

1. Download and extract the new tarball to /tmp/ldns-VERSION
2. Use the vendor-update skill (vendor/ldns/dist, contrib/ldns)
3. Check if any local patches need refreshing (see below)

Local patches applied on top of upstream:

  None. The resolv.conf comment parsing fix (FreeBSD) was merged
  upstream in ldns 1.8.4 (bugfix #237).

Notes:
  - The following directories are excluded from the in-tree copy
    and must be removed from the vendor worktree before committing:
      contrib/DNS-LDNS/   (Perl bindings)
    These dirs are also deleted from master via the subtree merge
    conflict resolution (keep-deleted).
  - ldns/util.h is generated by configure from ldns/util.h.in;
    the in-tree copy is the pre-generated version included by upstream.
  - Last imported: 1.8.4 (2026-06-10)
